           <div>
               <head>Recommended TEI Dictionary Structure</head>
               <p>This ODD document contains recommendations regarding the structure of VICAV Dictionary of Arabic Dialects as per team at INRIA with the following principles in mind:
               the dictionary should be the most optimally structured in terms of the TEI standards; the structure and contents of the lexical data contained therein; and its compatibility with LMF language encoding standards.
               </p>
               <div><!-- JB: SOME OF THIS IS INTENDED FOR WORKING DRAFTS AND NOTES FOR INRIA EDITORS (MYSELF AND LAURENT) AND MAY NOT BE INCLUDED IN FINAL VERSION OF ODD -->
                   <head>Recommended Changes to VICAV Upper Level Datastructures</head>
                   <p>
                      <list>
                          <item>Embedd <gi>gramGrp</gi> info within <gi>form</gi></item>
                      </list> 
                       
                   </p>
               </div>

               <div>
                   <!-- JB: 'gloss' not eliminated for the time being due to use in etymological dictionaries; (schematron rule limiting occurence to within etym); include explaination of rationale (in final) -->
                   
                   <head>Treatment of Variants</head>
                            
                   <!-- LMF: There are no examples in guidelines of plain orthography variations not having the @geographicalVariant or variatons being due to use of different scripts, table B.2 the closest thing to discussing issue;-->
                   
                   <p>There are some examples in the VICAV data that are not specifically labeled as such, but do seem to be instances of variant forms:</p>
                   <egXML xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/Examples">
                       
                   <entry xml:id="acma_001" numID="3077">
                       <form type="lemma">
                           <orth xml:lang="ar-arz-x-cairo-vicavTrans">ʔaʕma</orth>
                           <orth xml:lang="ar-arz-x-cairo-arabic">اعمى</orth>
                       </form>
                       
                       <gramGrp>
                           <gram type="pos">adjective</gram>
                           <gram type="semCat">physicalCharacteristic</gram><!-- JB: Isn't this more of the kind of content best fit for 'usg'? -->
                           <gram type="root" xml:lang="ar-arz-x-cairo-vicavTrans">ʕmy</gram><!-- JB: why @xml:lang here? -->
                       </gramGrp>
                       
                       <form type="inflected" ana="#adj_f"> 
                           <orth xml:lang="ar-arz-x-cairo-vicavTrans">ʕamya</orth>
                           <orth xml:lang="ar-arz-x-cairo-arabic">عميا</orth>
                       </form>
                       <!-- JB: What is the difference between these first two? -->
                       <form type="inflected" ana="#adj_f">
                           <orth xml:lang="ar-arz-x-cairo-vicavTrans">ʕamyāʔ</orth>
                           <orth xml:lang="ar-arz-x-cairo-arabic">عمياء</orth>
                       </form>
                       
                       <form type="inflected" ana="#adj_pl">
                           <orth xml:lang="ar-arz-x-cairo-vicavTrans">ʕumy</orth>
                           <orth xml:lang="ar-arz-x-cairo-arabic">عمي</orth>
                       </form>
                       <!-- JB: What is the difference between these last two? -->
                       <form type="inflected" ana="#adj_pl">
                           <orth xml:lang="ar-arz-x-cairo-vicavTrans">ʕimyān</orth>
                           <orth xml:lang="ar-arz-x-cairo-arabic">عميان</orth>
                       </form> 
                       <sense>
                           <cit type="translation" xml:lang="en">
                               <quote>blind</quote>
                           </cit> 
                           <cit type="translation" xml:lang="de">
                               <quote>blind</quote>
                           </cit>
                       </sense>
                       ...
                   </entry>
                   </egXML>
               </div>

             
